The paper deals with music information retrieval, specifically instrument recognition, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The use of convolutional neural networks for multi-label classification suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The incorporation of pitch information also suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
